Filmmaker and entertainment impresario, Ayo Shonaiya has recounted how Eedris Abdulkarim predicted Burna Boy’s Grammy win. Shonaiya, in his yet-to-be released documentary on Netflix ‘Afrobeats, the Backstory,’ said only a discerning few would remember that the ‘JagaJaga’ rapper predicted the Grammy win in one of his songs, Live in Yankee. In the song, Eedris had predicted himself winning a Grammy award after meeting with American music star and record label executive Sean Combs aka P.Diddy.   Razzy AG hints at collaboration with top music acts     Buga’s success has encouraged me to do more, Kizz Daniel     Yetunde Barnabas, Peter Olayinka expecting first child   Shonaiya married the prediction with Burna Boy’s win saying Eedris predicted the Grammy win but didn’t see the actual Nigerian act who will win. Burna Boy won his first Grammy in 2021 under the Best World Album category with his Twice As Tall album. Shonaiya has continued to create conversations around the Afrobeats genre, its progenitors, and practitioners through his 12-episode documentary.